article.headline: Louisiana-Monroe 66, North Texas 62
article.story: MONROE, La. (AP) -- Tony Hooper scored 18 points and Louisiana-Monroe hit eight 3-pointers in a 66-62 victory over North Texas on Saturday. The eight shots from long range gave the Warhawks 232 3-pointers this season, a new single-season record for the school. Lance Brasher and Jordan Payne each scored 14 points for ULM (16-10, 10-4 Sun Belt), which came back after trailing 35-27 at halftime. Jonas Brown added 11 points for the Warhawks. The game was tied at 60 when Hooper hit a baseline jumper with 31 seconds left. Payne's two free throws sealed it shortly after. Michael Sturns and Calvin Watson each scored 14 points for North Texas (16-9, 7-7), while Keith Wooden added 11. The ULM victory marked the first time since the 2001-02 season that the Warhawks had won their first 12 home games.
